The Pinetown community is calling for regular police patrol at the Dassenhoek High School. Two suspects have been arrested and police are searching for one more. Lethiwe Mdluli has more #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Pinetown community is calling for regular police patrol at the Dassenhoek High School following an armed robbery. Four pupils were stabbed and are recovering in hospital. READ: WATCH: KZN Education MEC speaks on disrupted academic year Two suspects have been arrested and police are searching for one more.  The suspected robbers who attacked pupils and teachers in Pinetown are former pupils of the school, according to KZN Education MEC, Kwazi Mshengu. He is now calling on communities to work with police to apprehend the suspects. #AllAngles #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/Dwj27OCVNW Meanwhile, according to KZN Education MEC Kwazi Mshengu, the suspected robbers are former pupils of the school. Mshengu is calling on communities to work with police to apprehend the suspects. eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli has been following this story.